      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NATIONAL GRID (2) carved over from wide out and boxed on strongly to finish 0.8 lengths away in second (23.02) behind Weblec Snip at Gawler. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings 12 times from 17 starts. Makes plenty of appeal. PHYLLOXERA FURY (6) has mixed form recently, finishing fourth (23.21) in a TG1-4W at Gawler latest but did run well two back when in the frame. Key player on best and worth another try. WEBLEC PEBBLES (4) ran below best last time finishing seventh (31.75) over 530m at Murray Bridge from Box 4. Boasts two wins from five starts out of this box. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. CERISE (8) comes into calculations after placing most recently.",
